# Phase 2 — Backend Architecture Plan

Backend data storage schema, FastAPI API contracts, and sprint deliverables.

---

## Data Storage

**Engine: SQLite** via Python's built-in `sqlite3` module — no ORM, no extra dependencies. Simple, file-based, zero config. Perfect for a hackathon MVP.

Database file: `backend/coherence.db` (auto-created on first run)

---

### Schema — 4 Tables

```mermaid
erDiagram
    knowledge_base {
        int id PK
        text content
        text updated_at
    }

    workflows {
        text id PK
        text name
        text description
        text nodes_json
        text edges_json
        text created_at
        text updated_at
    }

    workflow_runs {
        text id PK
        text workflow_id FK
        text lead_name
        text lead_persona
        text current_step
        text status
        text started_at
        text completed_at
    }

    execution_logs {
        int id PK
        text run_id FK
        text lead_name
        text event
        text log_type
        text timestamp
    }

    workflows ||--o{ workflow_runs : "has many"
    workflow_runs ||--o{ execution_logs : "has many"
```

### Table Details

#### `knowledge_base`
Stores the company context text. Only **one row** exists (singleton pattern — upsert on save).

| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| `id` | INTEGER PK | Always 1 (singleton) |
| `content` | TEXT | The company info text (max ~3000 chars) |
| `updated_at` | TEXT | ISO 8601 timestamp |

#### `workflows`
Stores workflow definitions built in the visual editor.

| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| `id` | TEXT PK | UUID string |
| `name` | TEXT | e.g. "Cold Outreach" |
| `description` | TEXT | Optional description |
| `nodes_json` | TEXT | JSON array of node objects from React Flow |
| `edges_json` | TEXT | JSON array of edge connections from React Flow |
| `created_at` | TEXT | ISO 8601 |
| `updated_at` | TEXT | ISO 8601 |

#### `workflow_runs`
Tracks each execution of a workflow against a lead/persona.

| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| `id` | TEXT PK | UUID string |
| `workflow_id` | TEXT FK | References `workflows.id` |
| `lead_name` | TEXT | e.g. "John Smith" |
| `lead_persona` | TEXT | e.g. "skeptical_cto", "busy_founder" |
| `current_step` | TEXT | Current node label/id |
| `status` | TEXT | `active` / `waiting` / `completed` / `failed` |
| `started_at` | TEXT | ISO 8601 |
| `completed_at` | TEXT | ISO 8601, nullable |

#### `execution_logs`
Chronological event log for each run — what the dashboard displays.

| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| `id` | INTEGER PK | Auto-increment |
| `run_id` | TEXT FK | References `workflow_runs.id` |
| `lead_name` | TEXT | Denormalized for fast log queries |
| `event` | TEXT | e.g. "Email Generated", "Workflow Started" |
| `log_type` | TEXT | `info` / `success` / `error` |
| `timestamp` | TEXT | ISO 8601 |

